        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="C7kQuruP18A7VfKhnydD-153" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;\(G_3\)&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="40" x="5210" y="-1160" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="C7kQuruP18A7VfKhnydD-159" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;spacing=0;spacingLeft=10;fontFamily=Roboto Mono;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DRoboto%2BMono;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ore&#39;s theorem&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;If \(G\) is a simple graph with \(n\) vertices with \(n \geq 3\) such that&lt;br&gt;\(\deg(u) + \deg(v) \geq n\) for every pair of nonadjacent vertices \(u\) and \(v\) in \(G\), then \(G\) has a Hamilton circuit.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="130" width="900" x="6040" y="-3070" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="C7kQuruP18A7VfKhnydD-160" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;spacing=0;spacingLeft=10;fontFamily=Roboto Mono;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DRoboto%2BMono;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;Sufficient conditions. It means that not all Hamiltonian circuit in a graph \(G\) with \(n\) vertices and \(n \geq 3\) has \(\deg(u) + \deg(v) \geq n\) for every pair of nonadjacent vertices \(u\) and \(v\)&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="880" x="6040" y="-3200" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="C7kQuruP18A7VfKhnydD-161" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;spacing=0;spacingLeft=10;fontFamily=Roboto Mono;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DRoboto%2BMono;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Bondy-Chvátal Theorem (1976)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;A graph is Hamiltonian if and only if its closure is Hamiltonian&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="880" x="6040" y="-2900" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="C7kQuruP18A7VfKhnydD-162" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;spacing=0;spacingLeft=10;fontFamily=Roboto Mono;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DRoboto%2BMono;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;The closure \(\operatorname{cl}(G)\) of a graph \(G\)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;with \(n\) vertices, obtained by repeatedly adding&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;a new edge \(uv\) connecting a nonadjacent pair of vertices&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\(u\) and \(v\) with \(\deg(v) + \deg(u) \geq n\)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;until no more pairs with this property can be found.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="160" width="840" x="6040" y="-2780" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="C7kQuruP18A7VfKhnydD-187" parent="1" style="shape=image;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;labelBackgroundColor=default;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/png,;" value="" vertex="1">
